{{Coord|25|01|40|N|121|31|53|E|display=title}} {{Infobox building |name = Mongolian and Tibetan Cultural Center |native_name = ËíôËóèÊñáÂåñ‰∏≠ÂøÉ |image = Mongolian and Tibetan Cultural Center Taipei Taiwan.jpg |opening = February 1993 |location = [[Da'an District, Taipei|Da'an]], [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]] |building_type = [[Cultural center]] |start_date = |completion_date = |cost = |roof = |top_floor = |architectural = |observatory = |floor_count = |floor_area = |elevator_count = |architect = |structural_engineer = |main_contractor = |management = [[Mongolian and Tibetan Affairs Commission]] |owner = |website = |references = }}
The '''Mongolian and Tibetan Cultural Center''' ({{zh|c=ËíôËóèÊñáÂåñ‰∏≠ÂøÉ|p=Mƒõng Z√†ng W√©nhu√† Zh≈çngxƒ´n}}) is a [[cultural center]] in [[Da'an District, Taipei|Da'an District]], [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]] under the administration of the [[Mongolian and Tibetan Affairs Commission]] of the [[Executive Yuan]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.mytravelguide.com/attractions/profile-101662448-Taiwan_Taipei_Mongolian_Tibetan_Cultural_Center.html | title=Mongolian & Tibetan Cultural Center | publisher=[http://www.mytravelguide.com/ MyTravelGuide] |accessdate=2014-02-20 }}</ref>
==History== The [[Government of the Republic of China|ROC government]] established the cultural center at the residence of the 7th [[Changkya Khutukhtu]] [[Lobsang Pelden Tenpe Dronme]] on February 1993.<ref name="mtac">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtac.gov.tw/epages.php?lang=5&page=136|title=Mongolian & Tibetan Culture Center|publisher=mtac.gov.tw|accessdate=2014-08-23}}</ref>
==Objectives== The Center has the following objectives:<ref name="mtac"/>
* Promote the [[Mongolia]]n and [[Tibet]]an cultures * Increase people's understanding of the Mongolian and Tibetan peoples * Advance Mongolian and Tibetan academic standards
==Facilities== The Center has the following facilities:<ref name="mtac"/>
===First and second floor=== * Exhibition area for cultural artifacts<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mytravelguide.com/attractions/profile-101662448-Taiwan_Taipei_Mongolian_Tibetan_Cultural_Center.html |title=Mongolian & Tibetan Cultural Center, Taipei |publisher=MyTravelGuide.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-21}}</ref>
===Third and fourth floor=== * Reading room * Lecture hall * Conference room * Memorial prayer hall for [[Lobsang Pelden Tenpe Dronme|the 7th Changkya Khutukhtu]]<ref name="mtac"/>
==Transportation== The Center is accessible within walking distance east from [[Guting Station]] of the [[Taipei Metro]].{{citation needed|date=February 2014}}
