As of 2006, the [[Ministry of Unification]] registered about 9,000 '''[[North Korea]]ns in South Korea'''. Many thousands of them escaped from North to South as a result of the North Korean famine of 1990s.<ref name=hmj>Hyung-Min Joo, [http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=1452129 "Underground Markets in North Korea"], September 4, 2009, APSA 2009 Toronto Meeting Paper </ref>
