North Koreans living in South Korea are often mistreated at schools, denied employment, and are subject to [[Ethnic issues in South Korea|other kinds of ethnic issues]] due to their being from North Korea.<ref name=YonhapNews>{{cite news|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/national/2011/10/09/4/0301000000AEN20111009000800315F.HTML | title = Only 20 N. Korean defectors work as public servants in S. Korea|date=October 19, 2011|accessdate=24 August 2012|work=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref><ref name=KoreaTimes>[http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2011/12/117_101561.html ''Korea Times'' (2011)]</ref><ref name=JapanFocus>{{cite web|url=http://www.japanfocus.org/-Sonia-Ryang/3771|title = North Koreans in South Korea: In Search of Their Humanity | date=18 June 2012|accessdate=24 August 2012|work=The Asia-Pacific Journal}}</ref> ==See also== * [[List of North Korean defectors in South Korea]] * [[North Korea‚ÄìSouth Korea relations]] * [[North Korean defectors]]
