{{Infobox language family |name=Nun |region=[[Western grassfields|Grassfields]] of western [[Cameroon]] |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic‚ÄìCongo]] |fam3=[[Benue‚ÄìCongo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Grassfields languages|Grassfields]] |fam6=[[Eastern Grassfields languages|Eastern]] |glotto=mbam1253 |glottorefname=Mbam‚ÄìNkam Nun }}
The '''Nun languages''' are a group of languages spoken by the [[Bamun people|Bamun]] and related peoples of the [[Western grassfields]] of [[Cameroon]].
The languages are [[Bamun language|Bamun]], [[Bamali language|Bamali]], [[Baba language|Baba]], [[Bamenyam language|Bamenyam]], [[Bafanji language|Bafanji]], [[Bangolan language|Bangolan]], [[Bambalang language|Bambalang]], [[Mungaka language|Mungaka]].
''Ethnologue'' adds [[Medumba language|Medumba]], a [[Bamileke language]].
