{{Infobox language |name=Pende |nativename=''Giphende'' |states=[[Democratic Republic of Congo]] |region=[[Bandundu Province]] |ethnicity=[[Pende people]] |speakers=420,000 |date=1991 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic‚ÄìCongo languages|Atlantic‚ÄìCongo]] |fam3=[[Benue‚ÄìCongo languages|Benue‚ÄìCongo]] |fam4=[[Bantoid languages|Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone L|Zone L]]) |fam6=[[Pende languages|Holu‚ÄìPende]] (L.10) |iso3=pem |glotto=phen1239 |glottorefname=Phende |guthrie=L.11 }} {{infobox ethnonym|Muphende|Baphende|Giphende}} '''Pende''' (Phende) is a [[Bantu language]] of the [[Democratic Republic of Congo|Congo]]. Giphende is spoken in Bandundu Province, in Gungu and Idiofa districts. The [[Pende people|Bapende]] used to call themselves ''Akwa Nzumba'' (in Kasai), ''Akwa Thunda'' (in Gungu), or ''Akwa Mbongo'' (in Idiofa).
