'''[[Polygamous]] [[marriages]]''' are recognized in '''[[Niger]]''' under customary law.<ref name=Niger>[http://genderindex.org/country/niger Niger:Family Code]</ref> The practice was present among indigenous populations but was greatly popularized after French Missionaries explored the region in 1901.<ref>{{cite book |last=Ekeh |first=Peter |date= |title=History of the Urhobo People of Niger Delta |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fFdeYB1lIPwC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false |location= |publisher=Urhobo Historical Society |page=157}}</ref> Today, it is estimated that over one third of [[Nigerien people|Nigerien]] women are in [[polygamous unions]].<ref name=Niger/>

